The Police Command in Borno State on Friday paraded a 46-year- old man who allegedly raped a 92-year-old woman. Parading the suspect at Maiduguri, the Commissioner of Police in the state, Abdu Umar said” on 24/03/2022 at about 1300hrs One Usman Haruna ‘M’ of Askira/Uba L.G.A of Borno State reported at Askira/Uba Division that one Zakariya
Ya’u ‘M’ 46yrs old of the same address forcefully had carnal knowledge/sexual intercourse with one Wamdubu Bello ‘F’ 92yrs old of the same address. Case is under investigation.” Also paraded by the police is One Clement Asuk ‘M’ of Akamkpa L.G.A of Cross River State at Kano Motor Park who was arrested On 30/03/2022 at about 07:22hrs. According to CP Umar, “the credible intelligence and surveillance team of the command who were on Morning Patrol Arrested him with the following exhibit.” “126 Anti Air Craft Ammunitions, 222 7.62mm of Life Ammunition, 517 of 7.62mm By 51 Life Ammunition, 7.62mm By 39 Life Ammunition, 2 Empty Magazines of Ak47, 4 Rpg Prepare Lent, 1 Hand Groaned, 5 Perfume, Application Form of Nigeria Navy, 3 Tooth Piece, 2 Small Carton of Fish,1 Anti Aircraft Ammunition Belt, 3 Pg – 7pm Preparelent, One Wrist Watch, 5 Rings, 3 Cowries, One Infinix Phone, One Charger, The Sum of ₦15,250 Nigerian Currency,” he said. “On the 31/1/2022 at about 1100hrs, one Mohammed Modu ‘m’ of Bama town, reported at Konduga Police Station that, on the same date at about 1200hrs, one Bilkisu Ali A.K.A Ummi ‘f’ 22yrs of Konduga IDP Camp also a volunteer CJTF Konduga LGA, took his 3yrs old daughter named Hadiza Modu ‘f’ with intend to go and sell to one Madam Joy ‘f’ surname unknown ‘f’ of Abia State who is now at large.” “The victim was rescued at Damaturu, Yobe State unhurt by the Police. A case under investigation.
SUSPECTS: (1) Modu Haske ‘m’ 45yrs old
(2) Abatcha Ali Mari ‘m’ 45yrs old
(3) Ali Mari ‘m’ 25yrs old
(4) Ali Yana Gajimi ‘m’ 21yrs old
(5) Musa Bulama Modu ‘m’ 30yrs old
